# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Project Overview

**{{PROJECT_NAME}}** - {{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}

Uses the **Harmony AI Framework** with three pillars:
- **Guardian Protocol** - Intent detection, agent routing, workflow protection
- **Sentinel System** - Error memory, circuit breaker (3 failures = stop), pattern learning
- **HQVF** - Use Case Verifiables (UCVs), triple validation (Dev+Test+QA)

## Essential Commands

```bash
/go                        # Session kickoff - ALWAYS run first
/harmony                   # Interactive menu (30 commands)
/harmony quick             # Fast validation (~30s)
/harmony full              # Complete audit (~2-5 min)
/harmony sentinel --reset  # Reset circuit breaker after failures
```

**Validation:** `/harmony duplicates`, `/harmony fix --apply`, `/harmony patterns`

**Reporting:** `/harmony report`, `/harmony tokens --breakdown`

**Profiles & Specialties:** `/harmony profiles --add <name>`, `/harmony specialties --add <name>`

**Quality Gates:** `/harmony ucv <story>`, `/harmony ucv --validate <story>`

Run `/harmony` to see all 30 commands with descriptions.

## Before Starting Work

1. Check `.claude/memory/workflow-state.json` for current phase (1-5)
2. Verify a story exists before coding (Guardian enforced)
3. Run `/harmony quick` after changes

## Key Rules

| Rule | Description |
|------|-------------|
| **No code without story** | Guardian blocks unauthorized changes |
| **UCV required** | Stories need Use Case Verifications |
| **Circuit breaker** | 3 failures = OPEN, needs reset |

